lspkind-nvim This tiny plugin adds vscode-like pictograms to neovim built-in lsp: гҒ“гҒ®е°ҸгҒ•гҒӘгғ—гғ©гӮ°гӮӨгғігҒҜгҖҒneovim гҒ®еҶ…и”ө lsp гҒ« vscode гҒ®гӮҲгҒҶгҒӘзөөж–Үеӯ—гӮ’иҝҪеҠ гҒ—гҒҫгҒҷпјҡ extensions/init.lua use { 'hrsh7th/nvim-cmp', config = function() require 'extensions.nvim-cmp' end, requires = { 'hrsh7th/cmp-nvim-lsp', 'hrsh7th/cmp-buffer', 'hrsh7th/cmp-path', 'hrsh7th/cmp-cmdline',
+ 'onsails/lspkind-nvim', (дёӯз•Ҙ) }
} extensions/nvim-cmp.lua cmp.setup { -- (дёӯз•Ҙ) formatting = { format = require('lspkind').cmp_format { mode = 'symbol', preset = 'codicons', }, },
} Highlighting & icon (copilot-cmp) Copilot's cmp source now has a builtin highlight group CmpItemKindCopilot. To add an icon to copilot for lspkind, simply add copilot to your lspkind symbol map. Copilot гҒ® cmp гӮҪгғјгӮ№гҒ«гҖҒзө„гҒҝиҫјгҒҝгҒ®гғҸгӮӨгғ©гӮӨгғҲгӮ°гғ«гғјгғ—CmpItemKindCopilotгҒҢиҝҪеҠ гҒ•гӮҢгҒҫгҒ—гҒҹгҖӮ lspkind гҒ® copilot гҒ«гӮўгӮӨгӮігғігӮ’иҝҪеҠ гҒҷгӮӢгҒ«гҒҜгҖҒlspkind гҒ®гӮ·гғігғңгғ«гғһгғғгғ—гҒ« copilot гӮ’иҝҪеҠ гҒҷгӮӢгҒ гҒ‘гҒ§гҒҷгҖӮ Alternatively, you can add Copilot to the lspkind symbol_map within the cmp format function. гҒҫгҒҹгҒҜгҖҒcmp гғ•гӮ©гғјгғһгғғгғҲй–ўж•°еҶ…гҒ§ lspkind symbol_mapгҒ« Copilot гӮ’иҝҪеҠ гҒҷгӮӢгҒ“гҒЁгӮӮгҒ§гҒҚгҒҫгҒҷгҖӮ extensions/nvim-cmp.lua cmp.setup { -- (дёӯз•Ҙ) formatting = { format = require('lspkind').cmp_format { mode = 'symbol', preset = 'codicons',
+ symbol_map = { Copilot = 'п„“' }, }, },
} before after (Plus: cmp-path) (Plus: cmp-cmdline)

